                            <comment id="13311911" author="tadayosi" created="Wed, 26 Oct 2016 00:03:51 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;As this is essentially the same issue as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-6136&quot; title=&quot;got &amp;quot;java.net.SocketException: Invalid argument&amp;quot; exception&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ENTESB-6136&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ENTESB-6136&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and this one doesn&apos;t happen with Fuse 6.2.1 / 6.3.0, let&apos;s mark it as resolved (as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-6136&quot; title=&quot;got &amp;quot;java.net.SocketException: Invalid argument&amp;quot; exception&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ENTESB-6136&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ENTESB-6136&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-6136&quot; title=&quot;got &amp;quot;java.net.SocketException: Invalid argument&amp;quot; exception&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ENTESB-6136&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ENTESB-6136&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has also been identified and fixed, and the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-6136&quot; title=&quot;got &amp;quot;java.net.SocketException: Invalid argument&amp;quot; exception&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ENTESB-6136&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ENTESB-6136&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should probably fix the issue for 6.1.&lt;/p&gt;

